Package: mga
Type: Package
Title: Microbial Genetic Analysis for amplicon data
Version: 0.1.0
Date: 2023-11-28
Author: c(person(c("Erika","Y."), "Lin", email = "erikalin26@gmail.com", role = c("aut","cre")))
Maintainer: Erika Lin <erikalin26@gmail.com>
URL: https://github.com/ErikaYLin/mga
Description: A core function for microbiome analysis by processing raw genetic sequencing data to produce taxonomic classification, phylogenetic and co-occurrence networks, and metrics of community structure. Also featured are additional functions for common downstream analyses.
    The package is based on methods used in Callahan et al. (2016) <doi.org/10.12688/f1000research.8986.2>.
License: GPL-3
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
biocViews:
Depends: R (>= 4.0.0), dada2, phyloseq
Imports: stringr, DECIPHER, Biostrings, phangorn, igraph, methods
Suggests: ggplot2, knitr, rmarkdown, nlme, CooccurrenceAffinity
